#MEM id=triple-pass-protocol source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Psychology/Daniel_Kahneman/skills/operating-system/triple-pass-protocol/SKILL.md
M|triple-pass-protocol|name: triple-pass-protocol
M|triple-pass-protocol|description: Kahneman's pre-delivery validation gate. Three passes — Audit, Critique (adversarial), Fix — before any verdict is issued. Stark never sees the process, only the final verdict.
M|triple-pass-protocol|version: 1.0.0
M|triple-pass-protocol|A bias audit issued without internal challenge is itself subject to bias. This protocol forces Kahneman to audit his own audit before delivering a verdict — catching overconfident 🟢 verdicts and unde
M|triple-pass-protocol|Run the full bias checklist against the agt's output. Name every bias found, where it appears, and what it distorts. Draft the verdict (🟢 / 🟡 / 🔴) and the correction.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Stop before delivering. Become the adversarial reviewer. Ask every question on this list:
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Checklist completeness:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Did I run all 8 bias items — or did I stop at the first 2-3 I found?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Did I check for biases that favour the output (confirmation bias in my own audit)?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Did I check the outside view — did I actually look up a base rate, or just accept the agt's number?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Verdict calibration:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is this 🟢 too easy? Would a 🔴 have been more appropriate if I'm honest?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is this 🔴 too strict? Is the bias material enough to block, or is this a 🟡 caution?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Does my correction actually remove the bias — or does it just soften the language?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Correction specificity:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is the correction a specific reframe the agt can act on immediately?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Or is it vague guidance ("consider revising") that puts the burden back on the agt to figure out what I mean?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Escalation check:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Am I escalating to Marcus for a reason that's within agt scope?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is this genuinely a 🔴 strategic issue, or a 🟡 that I'm over-weighting?
M|triple-pass-protocol|Revise anything the critique found. Sharpen vague corrections into specific rewrites. Recalibrate the verdict if the critique revealed over/under-weighting. Then deliver.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Stark sees the Pass 3 output only. Never narrate the triple-pass process.